details.description: ¡Descubre los auténticos sabores de Colombia en Roasted Tinto! Te invitamos a disfrutar de una experiencia gastronómica única que celebra las ricas tradiciones culinarias de Colombia. En nuestro establecimiento, ofrecemos una deliciosa selección de platos icónicos como arepas, empanadas, maduros, guacamole y mucho más. Cada bocado te transportará a la esencia de nuestra cultura y sazón. ¡Ven y déjate enamorar por la auténtica cocina colombiana!

reviews_data.review_text: Great prices, great people, great product. Absolutely will be back!
Twas bussin
Excellent food and service.
Excelente
The atmosphere is really nice and inviting. The coffee is good, but the cheesecake with the fruit was my favorite! It’s made to perfection. My son got a brownie and that was good as well.
Customer service was great & prices were reasonable! I will definitely be coming again :)
Excellent services, Jaime is an excellent person and he do the best bread.

Went to this Colombian Cafe this morning. Great little cafe with small bakery items like empanadas and arepas as well as small cakes and bread. It was right next to a laundromat connected actually so if you’re doing laundry you can go right next store for some food but you didn’t even notice the laundromat was right next store.

Colombian wife approved of the food! So you know it’s legit.
I only tried the beef and chicken empanadas. They were delicious and very reasonably priced!
A friendly welcome and delicious baked goods.
Buena antencion solamente pero la comida no la recomiendo

Driving by I couldn’t help but notice this gem of a place.  Stopped to check it out, and did not leave empty handed and with the desire to come, have been in 4 times within the last 2 weeks.  The chicken empanadas were delicious, stuffed with more chicken than potatoes.  It is so hard for me to find cheese empanada and they always have them, and always fresh.  I had to indulge with the big size chocolatina jet.
The place is super clean and well taken care of.
Love my mornings with their empanadas and cafecito con leche y el chismecito, of course.

I want to take the time to highlight businesses that really adhere to high standards. What a great spot! The coffee is fresh with many creative seasonal options, pastries are delicious, and the meal food (arepas etc.) are done well. I’m always grateful to find quality spots. Definitely recommend checking them out!
Darling place to try!
Great food, at reasonable prices. The empanadas were crispy and well season, excellent flavor
The arepa is amazing, try it and you won't be disappointed.
Excellent attention.
Hidden gem, very good coffee and delicious Colombian baked goods. Very clean place and nice staff! Recommended.
Love this place! The coffee was so tasty and the Pan de Bonos 10/10!! ♥️
Very nice owner , clean and very professional, if you’re looking for a taste of Colombia this is your place .

Place is located attached to the laundry, we almost passed it. Great service and delicious flavors. Very authentic colombian coffee (one of the best ones we have tried). Atmosphere is very comfortable to pass the time and "chismear".

If you are interested they have Colombian snacks too.
Excelente servico
Muy excelente servicio

I just went to the bakery for the first time and everything was very welcoming.
- Great bread
- Great people

I will definitely come back and buy more!!
Great coffee and empanadas

The food was good and service excellent 👌
Access to the parking lot little bit difficult

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Empanada, Stuffed Arepa, Beef Empanadas, Pulled Pork

reviews_data.review_text: Nice place. 100% Colombian Coffee.

Great costumer service.

The place was clean when I visited.

Plenty of parking available.

The atmosphere it’s great, nice decor.

The food truck has great options and the stuffed arepa was so good!

They have coffee, empanadas, pan de bono, juice (jugo hit).

Prices are pretty good.
Thats not colombian, that's Venezuelan
Very delicious arepa
Excelente el sabor de las Empanadas
11 am and is close

I ordered 3 beef empanadas. This was my second time ever trying an empanada and it was so yummy! It also came with a sauce on the side that was delicious! I found this place on a whim and decided to stop by and try it. I’m so glad I did. The service was quick and nice. I can’t wait to come back!
